<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-14892] Possible corruption in compressed files with uncompressed chunks</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-14892</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When deciding to switch to writing a chunk uncompressed in a compressed file (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-10520&quot; title=&quot;Compressed writer and reader should support non-compressed data.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-10520&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-10520&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) and that chunk is smaller than the full chunk size (only currently happens in the last chunk of the file), it may very rarely happen that the chunk is:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;bigger than the compression limit when compressed&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;smaller than the compression limit when left uncompressed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;If this happens the writer will write it uncompressed, but the reader will treat it as compressed and fail when attempting to read it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Such chunks should be padded with 0s to the minimum uncompressed size.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
